HEADWORD: Niding
<hw>Ni"ding</hw> <pr>(n⟦imac⟧"d⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>nithing</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[AS.
<ets>n⟦imac⟧⟦edh⟧ing</ets>, fr. <ets>n⟦imac⟧⟦edh⟧</ets> wickedness,
malice, hatred.]</ety> <def>A coward; a dastard; -- a term of utmost
opprobrium.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He is worthy to be called a <qex>niding</qex>.</q>
